Jose Mourinho singled out Scott McTominay for praise following Manchester United&lsquo;s win over Huddersfield on Saturday. Goals from Romelu Lukaku and Alexis Sanchez, his first for the club since his move from Arsenal, helped Mourinho&rsquo;s side bounce back from their midweek defeat at Tottenham and record a routine 2-0 win. The United manager caused a surprise with his starting XI, however, dropping Paul Pogba to the bench and handing 19-year-old McTominay only his second Premier League start of the season. &lsquo;I made a few changes thinking about the characteristics of this game,&rsquo; said Mourinho.<br />
<br />
&lsquo;I think this kid [McTominay] has a great desire to recover the ball when the team is not in possession. &lsquo;He&rsquo;s a kid that chases the ball, that tries to recover high up the pitch and when he has the ball it is always simple. &lsquo;And against opponents like Huddersfield, so close and with so many bodies behind the ball, the simplicity sometimes is genius.&rsquo;
